-- Arrium Names Roberts to Succeed Plummer as Chief Executive
-- B y   S o r a y a   P e r m a t a s a r i
-- 2013-02-18T02:55:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-18/arrium-names-roberts-to-succeed-plummer-as-chief-executive.html
Arrium Ltd. , Australia’s second-
largest steel prodcer, promoted Andrew Roberts, 46, the head its
mining consumables unit, to succeed  Geoff Plummer  as chief
executive officer.  Roberts will join the company’s board of directors
immediately as deputy managing director and is expected to take
up the chief executive’s role in the first quarter of fiscal
2014, Sydney-based Arrium said today in a statement.  Arrium last year rebuffed a A$1.2 billion ($1.24 billion)
takeover bid from a Noble Group Ltd. and Posco-led consortium,
The company, which has a market value of A$1.7 billion, relied
on iron ore sales for more than half its earnings in the year
ended June 30 last year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
